=== Other ===
Until {{ill|lt=Heisei|Q234510|WD=Q234510|1=Heisei era}} 18 (2006), a fireworks display dedicated to the shrine was held every {{ill|lt=July|Q121|WD=Q121|1=July}} during the summer festival, but from the following year onward, while the summer festival continued as before, the fireworks display was discontinued. {{Citation needed|date=January 2012|The {{ill|lt=Akashi Fireworks Festival Pedestrian Bridge Accident|Q4700349|WD=Q4700349|1=Akashi pedestrian bridge accident}} that occurred in Heisei 13 (2001) is believed to have had no small influence.}}

